title: Declare variable key in the get_user example
bodyText:
As the variable key is not defined, the example could generate a little of confusion in my opinion.
If we don't want to add more complexity using format(), we should be also able to just do key = "user.{user_id}.

title: Explain difference between PUT & PATCH
bodyText: I think some developers get confused between PUT & PATCH. This Laracasts comment hopes to provide a clear distinction between the two.

title: Update service discovery section to include consul, etcd, and additional details
Change AP wording for clarity
bodyText:
I think that the description for AP should be changed. It currently says that the most recent version of the data might not be the latest.
The explanation of Consistency uses the same word, recent.
I have changed AP to qualify 'recent' as being the most recent data available on the node

title: Add Grab Engineering Blog link
bodyText: Grab is one of the largest transport companies in South-east Asia, and they handle 2.3 million rides daily. Their Engineering Blog content focuses on how they handle the scale of their business and is suitable for learning system design.

title: Add automated testing
bodyText: The goal of this change is to have Travis-CI automatically run flake8 tests on every pull request. This will help contributors know if their submissions are going to break the build. To turn on this free service, you would need to do steps 1 and 2 of https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/getting-started/

title: Convert all .py files to be valid Python
bodyText:
raise NotImplementedError('Please replace this line with your code...') signals to the user where they need to put their code.
This approach enables the codebase to be tested with lint tools like flake8, pyflakes, pylint, etc.

title: ja: Fix typo
bodyText:
WHY
About native there is a shake of the notation of "ネーティブ" and "ネイティブ" in README-ja.
I think that it is probably typo. 🤔

original contents:

$ grep -ir "native" ./README.md 
./README.md:RPC is focused on exposing behaviors.  RPCs are often used for performance reasons with internal communications, as you can hand-craft native calls to better fit your use cases.
./README.md:Choose a native library (aka SDK) when:


ja:

$ grep -ir "ネイティブ" ./README-ja.md 
./README-ja.md:ネイティブライブラリー (aka SDK) を呼ぶのは以下の時:
$ grep -ir "ネーティブ" ./README-ja.md 
./README-ja.md:RPCは振る舞いを公開することに焦点を当てています。RPCは内部通信パフォーマンスを理由として使われることが多いです。というのも、使用する状況に合わせてネーティブコールを自作することができるからです。

WHAT
FIx typo.(s/ネーティブ/ネイティブ/g)

title: Fix coding errors
bodyText:
The function parameter in reducer(self, key, value): is value (without an s) but the function body uses values with an s which creates an undefined name.  Solution: change the function parameter from value to values.  Discovered via #93
Also fixed a copy-and-paste error and a missing comma error.
